  <title translate="true">Tip #46</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Heading3"><text styleclass="Heading3" translate="true">Tip of the Day</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:58px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="TipOfTheDayBulb.jpg" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:328px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">One can associate an individual method of a class with a package other than that in which its class resides. Such methods are termed &apos;loose methods&apos; and they can be very useful if you want to extend base classes from your own packages.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Loose methods are highlighted in magenta in the class and system browser methods list.</text><snippet src="Tip_Of_The_Day_Footer"/></para>
